{"BLADDER":[{"def":"A bag or sac in animals, which serves as the receptacle of some fluid; as, the urinary bladder; the gall bladder; -- applied especially to the urinary bladder, either within the animal, or when taken out and inflated with air.","pos":""},{"def":"A distended, membranaceous pericarp.","pos":""}],"BLADDERWORT":[{"def":"A genus (Utricularia) of aquatic or marshy plants, which usually bear numerous vesicles in the divisions of the leaves.","pos":""}],"BLADDERY":[{"def":"Having bladders; also, resembling a bladder.","pos":""}],"BLADE":[{"def":"The principal rafters of a roof.","pos":""},{"def":"The four large shell plates on the sides, and the five large ones of the middle, of the carapace of the sea turtle, which yield the best tortoise shell.","pos":""}],"BLADED":[{"def":"Composed of long and narrow plates, shaped like the blade of a knife.","pos":""}],"BLADEFISH":[{"def":"A long, thin, marine fish of Europe (Trichiurus lepturus); the ribbon fish.","pos":""}],"BLADY":[{"def":"Consisting of blades.","pos":""}]}